The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with estimating the 3D pose of an individual's upper limbs from a chest-mounted depth camera. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as SVM, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper focuses on everyday interactions with objects, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
